column11: Emily invested $85200 in two different accounts and has a cat named Uni. One account earns 2% annual interest, the other earns 5% annual interest, and her cat stole 5% of her total investment before she invested. And her mom invested $4110 in five accounts and has a cat named Moe. One account earns 1% annual interest, and Moe stole 85% more than Uni. If the total interest earned after one year is $340, how much did Moe steal? Please answer in one integer
